# Cucumber Feature File Patterns

## Feature File Structure

### Standard Feature Template
```gherkin
@ModuleName @Sanity @All @allGet/@allPost @Execution
Feature: This feature file contains testcases for {HTTP_METHOD} endpoint {API_NAME}

  @PositiveScenario
  Scenario: TC_01 {API_NAME} - status code positive case
    Given I set up base URI for transactions
    When I set up request specification
      |HeaderName|HeaderValue|
      |Content-Type|application/json|
      |Accept|*/*|
      |Accept-Encoding|gzip,deflate, br|
      |Connection|keep-alive|
    And I {action} the request with "{payloadName}" payload with dynamic access token and query parameters
      |Query         |Value         |
      |access_token  |ACCESS_TOKEN  |
    Then I should see the response code as "200"
    And the fields in response should match with expected values
      | JPath     | Value |
      | $.Result  | true  |
    And verify response headers
      | HeaderName    | HeaderValue                 |
      | Content-Type  | text/html; charset=UTF-8    |
      | Server        | Bizom                       |
      | Connection    | keep-alive                  |
    And verify response time is less than "1200" milliseconds
    And I store the response as "{responseName}" name using full path
```

## Common Step Patterns

### Request Setup
- `Given I set up base URI for transactions`
- `When I set up request specification` with header table
- `And I send the GET/POST request to "{endpoint}" endpoint`

### Authentication
- `And I send the GET/POST request to "{endpoint}" endpoint with dynamic access token, path and query parameters`
- Use `ACCESS_TOKEN` as query parameter value for dynamic token resolution

### Response Validation
- `Then I should see the response code as "{statusCode}"`
- `And the fields in response should match with expected values` with JPath table
- `And verify response headers` with expected headers table
- `And verify response time is less than "{time}" milliseconds`

### Data Storage
- `And I store the response as "{name}" name using full path`

## Tagging Conventions
- `@BizomWebAPI` - BizomWebAPI suite tests
- `@Execution` - IntegrationAPI and RetailerAPI suite tests
- `@ModuleName` - API module (Users, Orders, Sales, etc.)
- `@Sanity` - Sanity test scenarios
- `@allGet` - GET request scenarios
- `@allPost` - POST request scenarios
- `@PositiveScenario` - Positive test cases
- `@NegativeScenario` - Negative test cases